1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:01:05,128 --> 00:01:07,046
It's itchy and prickly, right?

3
00:01:11,342 --> 00:01:13,887
Take off your bag
and sit against the wall.

4
00:01:17,557 --> 00:01:20,268
Sit tight. I'll fix you up in no time.

5
00:01:20,351 --> 00:01:22,103
Oh, I'm honestly okay.

6
00:01:22,187 --> 00:01:23,354
You're not okay.

7
00:01:23,438 --> 00:01:26,065
I thought Si-won was home.
That's why I stopped by.

8
00:01:26,149 --> 00:01:27,859
Your eye…

9
00:01:27,942 --> 00:01:28,860
You have

10
00:01:30,153 --> 00:01:31,738
a cursed splinter in your eye.

11
00:01:31,821 --> 00:01:33,698
-Sorry?
-A cursed splinter.

12
00:01:33,781 --> 00:01:36,993
You have to yank that out
for that red eye to get better.

13
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:46,002
Hold it tight like this.

14
00:01:46,502 --> 00:01:49,130
And hold this in your mouth.
Take a full mouthful.

15
00:01:50,215 --> 00:01:51,216
A mouthful.

16
00:01:53,092 --> 00:01:55,136
Swish it around and spit it out here.

17
00:01:55,637 --> 00:01:56,471
Spit it out.

18
00:01:58,056 --> 00:01:58,932
Give it to me.

19
00:01:59,432 --> 00:02:00,266
Okay.

20
00:02:24,165 --> 00:02:25,625
Feels a bit better now, huh?

21
00:02:30,296 --> 00:02:32,966
What the heck?
This is better than the hospital.

22
00:02:33,049 --> 00:02:35,009
You're seriously comparing me to a doctor?

23
00:02:35,093 --> 00:02:37,178
I'm completely different from a doctor.

24
00:02:37,262 --> 00:02:38,429
How are you different?

25
00:02:38,513 --> 00:02:43,434
Anyone can become a doctor
if they grind hard enough.

26
00:02:43,518 --> 00:02:46,104
But people like us?
You've actually gotta be gifted.

27
00:02:46,938 --> 00:02:48,147
An innate gift.

28
00:02:48,731 --> 00:02:50,191
You know what I mean, don't you?

29
00:02:53,903 --> 00:02:56,781
Well, go see that girl
who ran away from home.

30
00:02:58,491 --> 00:03:00,034
SI-WON

31
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:08,167
Goodbye, ma'am.

32
00:03:08,751 --> 00:03:11,337
Tell her not to skip her meals.

33
00:03:46,622 --> 00:03:49,584
What? You fell back asleep that quickly?

34
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:50,543
Yeah.

35
00:03:50,626 --> 00:03:51,836
Aren't you cold?

36
00:03:52,337 --> 00:03:54,339
You should sleep at home
when it's this cold.

37
00:03:54,422 --> 00:03:55,798
It's even snowing outside.

38
00:03:55,882 --> 00:03:57,675
It's better than smelling like incense.

39
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:59,844
Wait, it's snowing? In March?

40
00:04:08,728 --> 00:04:09,729
Si-won.

41
00:04:10,396 --> 00:04:12,690
Should I join the coding club too?

42
00:04:28,206 --> 00:04:30,541
Hey, Do Hye-ryung!

43
00:04:31,709 --> 00:04:34,879
-Hurry! We'll be late if we miss the bus.
-We won't be late.

44
00:04:34,962 --> 00:04:36,297
Slow down. We won't be late.

45
00:04:36,381 --> 00:04:37,256
Seriously!

46
00:04:37,757 --> 00:04:38,591
Hey!

47
00:04:40,426 --> 00:04:41,260
Hey.

48
00:04:46,516 --> 00:04:48,184
Whoa, hey!

49
00:04:51,062 --> 00:04:52,355
What are you doing?

50
00:04:52,438 --> 00:04:54,774
-Let's take our time.
-What's with you?

51
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:57,193
Hey, the bus…

52
00:04:59,487 --> 00:05:00,530
Han Gi-tae?

53
00:05:01,114 --> 00:05:01,948
Huh?

54
00:05:05,076 --> 00:05:06,285
You like him, don't you?

55
00:05:07,537 --> 00:05:08,371
No, I don't.

56
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,164
Want me to tell him?

57
00:05:10,248 --> 00:05:12,250
Hey, no. Don't ever tell him.

58
00:05:14,377 --> 00:05:16,587
-Are you close with Gi-tae?
-Yeah.

59
00:05:16,671 --> 00:05:18,297
He joined our club, remember?

60
00:05:19,215 --> 00:05:20,174
I was right.

61
00:05:21,551 --> 00:05:23,010
You like him, huh?

62
00:05:23,803 --> 00:05:25,471
Don't worry. I'll keep your secret.

63
00:05:26,806 --> 00:05:27,974
You mean it?

64
00:05:29,225 --> 00:05:31,060
For as long as you keep my secret.

65
00:05:32,353 --> 00:05:33,855
-There you are.
-Goodness.

66
00:05:33,938 --> 00:05:34,981
-Over here.
-Move over.

67
00:05:35,064 --> 00:05:35,898
It's warm.

68
00:05:35,982 --> 00:05:37,859
Sit here. It's a heated seat.

69
00:05:38,443 --> 00:05:39,944
Oh dear.

70
00:05:40,027 --> 00:05:41,112
Sorry about that.

71
00:05:43,823 --> 00:05:45,366
Thank you, girls.

72
00:05:51,706 --> 00:05:55,376
I was half-asleep, so I wasn't sure
if I really smelled incense,

73
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:56,919
but did you go inside my house?

74
00:05:58,504 --> 00:05:59,464
You're scary good.

75
00:06:03,176 --> 00:06:04,802
You didn't pick up your phone.

76
00:06:04,886 --> 00:06:08,264
It was freezing,
so I figured you'd be sleeping at home.

77
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:10,808
Your mom told me to come in
so she could fix my eye.

78
00:06:10,892 --> 00:06:13,978
It's one thing to come over.
I told you not to play along with her.

79
00:06:14,061 --> 00:06:15,188
Why don't you listen?

80
00:06:15,271 --> 00:06:16,314
I'm sorry.

81
00:06:18,357 --> 00:06:20,067
But it actually worked this time.

82
00:06:20,568 --> 00:06:23,070
Look. It was super red,
but now you can't even tell.

83
00:06:24,614 --> 00:06:26,532
You're doing this just to annoy me.

84
00:06:26,616 --> 00:06:29,076
This wouldn't have happened
if you'd picked up.

85
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,703
Hey, are you blaming me?

86
00:06:30,786 --> 00:06:33,998
If I don't, just go without me.
I never asked you to come with me.

87
00:06:38,294 --> 00:06:39,128
All right.

88
00:06:39,212 --> 00:06:42,715
From now on, I'll just ignore your mom,
no matter what she says, okay?

89
00:06:43,216 --> 00:06:44,050
Promise.

90
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:47,887
You actually like hanging out with someone
who drinks and calls it shaman stuff?

91
00:06:48,638 --> 00:06:50,223
My sincerest apologies.

92
00:06:50,723 --> 00:06:51,724
Okay?

93
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:55,770
OUR FACULTY AND STAFF SUPPORT
THE NEW BEGINNINGS OF ALL NEW STUDENTS

94
00:06:55,853 --> 00:06:56,938
Good morning.

95
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:01,817
Hey, Kwon Si-won.

96
00:07:03,402 --> 00:07:04,278
Si-won.

97
00:07:04,362 --> 00:07:07,031
Have you decided what you're doing
for the app contest?

98
00:07:07,114 --> 00:07:08,658
I thought about it yesterday.

99
00:07:08,741 --> 00:07:10,826
-Let's talk about it in the clubroom.
-Sure.

100
00:07:14,372 --> 00:07:16,165
Why don't you join the coding club?

101
00:07:16,249 --> 00:07:17,917
You're around this genius every day.

102
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,418
Oh, can I also--

103
00:07:19,502 --> 00:07:21,379
She's not into tinkering with machines.

104
00:07:22,547 --> 00:07:23,381
Really?

105
00:07:23,923 --> 00:07:25,132
Then what are you into?

106
00:07:27,009 --> 00:07:29,095
She's… into shamanism.

107
00:07:30,763 --> 00:07:33,599
Shamanism? Like fortunetelling and stuff?

108
00:07:34,559 --> 00:07:35,768
Do my fortune too.

109
00:07:36,269 --> 00:07:37,979
Hey, Hee-jin.

110
00:07:44,485 --> 00:07:47,446
Hey. You're actually on time for once.

111
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:50,491
Teacher kept bitching about how I'm dead
if I'm late again.

112
00:07:51,075 --> 00:07:54,787
I skipped breakfast to leave hella early.
Wanna hit the cafeteria?

113
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:56,872
Si-won. You should come with us.

114
00:08:01,669 --> 00:08:02,503
Go on ahead.

115
00:08:05,256 --> 00:08:06,215
Let's hurry.

116
00:08:30,948 --> 00:08:33,409
Oh, I have to go to my club today.

117
00:08:33,492 --> 00:08:34,535
Should I wait?

118
00:08:34,619 --> 00:08:35,703
Si-won.

119
00:08:36,537 --> 00:08:37,538
Let's go.

120
00:08:38,456 --> 00:08:39,498
Just go without me.

121
00:08:48,924 --> 00:08:52,219
Why do you keep buying so much alcohol
when you're drinking alone?

122
00:08:52,303 --> 00:08:54,305
I'm not drinking alone.

123
00:08:54,388 --> 00:08:57,141
It's not like you're drinking
with your high school daughter.

124
00:08:58,976 --> 00:09:01,228
You know that's not what I mean.

125
00:09:01,312 --> 00:09:03,648
If you're so curious,
why not come over to my place?

126
00:09:03,731 --> 00:09:04,565
My goodness.

127
00:09:04,649 --> 00:09:06,734
Don't try that joke on me,
you quack shaman.

128
00:09:06,817 --> 00:09:08,319
A quack?

129
00:09:12,114 --> 00:09:14,200
Does it seem like a joke to you?

130
00:09:33,719 --> 00:09:36,013
You really think you can hide from me?

131
00:09:42,228 --> 00:09:43,771
Hello, ma'am.

132
00:09:43,854 --> 00:09:45,106
-Hello.
-Yeah.

133
00:09:45,690 --> 00:09:46,607
Where's my daughter?

134
00:09:47,274 --> 00:09:48,651
Her club will finish late.

135
00:09:48,734 --> 00:09:50,653
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

136
00:09:51,153 --> 00:09:53,447
Wanna come over to my place?

137
00:09:55,157 --> 00:09:55,991
No, ma'am.

138
00:09:56,826 --> 00:09:57,660
Why's that?

139
00:09:59,704 --> 00:10:03,499
I bet you're itching
to come over to my place right now.

140
00:10:05,209 --> 00:10:06,127
Goodbye, ma'am.

141
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:25,438
Goodness me, that hurts.

142
00:10:25,938 --> 00:10:27,231
Damn it.

143
00:10:27,732 --> 00:10:29,775
Oh dear.

144
00:10:32,653 --> 00:10:35,322
"Awards. Minister's Award, one team."

145
00:10:35,406 --> 00:10:38,576
"Governor's Award, one team.
Superintendent's Award, two teams."

146
00:10:38,659 --> 00:10:41,162
Even fourth place looks good
on college applications.

147
00:10:42,872 --> 00:10:44,081
You'll win for us, right?

148
00:10:44,165 --> 00:10:46,292
Once we pick a theme,
coding should be easy.

149
00:10:47,293 --> 00:10:50,629
Then while we're prepping for the contest,
I'll do Si-won's snack runs.

150
00:10:50,713 --> 00:10:52,715
I'll also help with UI design.

151
00:10:52,798 --> 00:10:54,008
Then I will

152
00:10:55,384 --> 00:10:56,677
grant you one wish.

153
00:10:56,761 --> 00:10:58,971
Like Si-won would ever need
anything from you.

154
00:10:59,054 --> 00:11:00,431
But her friend might.

155
00:11:01,182 --> 00:11:02,850
She keeps glancing at you every day.

156
00:11:02,933 --> 00:11:05,269
-I see Do Hye-ryung has good taste.
-Hey.

157
00:11:06,228 --> 00:11:07,271
Be careful.

158
00:11:07,772 --> 00:11:08,898
She's one scary girl.

159
00:11:08,981 --> 00:11:11,484
-Why do you say that?
-Her mom's a shaman.

160
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:15,488
And not just any shaman,
but a hella famous whack job shaman.

161
00:11:16,489 --> 00:11:19,033
-This bastard's lying again.
-I'm serious, dipshit.

162
00:11:19,116 --> 00:11:21,911
My cousin went to Baekun Middle School.

163
00:11:21,994 --> 00:11:25,790
I heard the daughter of a crazy shaman
who drove her husband to death went there.

164
00:11:26,499 --> 00:11:27,374
And that

165
00:11:28,292 --> 00:11:29,168
is Do Hye-ryung.

166
00:11:30,711 --> 00:11:31,545
For real?

167
00:11:34,089 --> 00:11:36,008
-Hey, I think it's true.
-Yeah.

168
00:11:36,091 --> 00:11:38,594
That's why you brought up
shamanism earlier, right?

169
00:11:39,512 --> 00:11:41,639
That's enough. Let's brainstorm the theme.

170
00:11:41,722 --> 00:11:42,807
Shamanism.

171
00:11:44,058 --> 00:11:46,185
-Hey, I like shamanism.
-For the love of…

172
00:11:46,685 --> 00:11:48,813
You don't wanna do the contest?
Should we quit?

173
00:11:48,896 --> 00:11:51,857
I'm talking about what you said, Gi-tae.

174
00:11:51,941 --> 00:11:52,817
What do you mean?

175
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:55,945
You just said that you'd grant any wish.

176
00:11:56,028 --> 00:11:58,489
What comes to mind
when it comes to shamanism? Saju.

177
00:11:58,572 --> 00:12:01,951
So an app where you enter your saju,
make a wish,

178
00:12:02,034 --> 00:12:04,203
and the wish somehow gets granted--

179
00:12:04,286 --> 00:12:05,412
Hey!

180
00:12:05,496 --> 00:12:06,664
Don't get carried away.

181
00:12:06,747 --> 00:12:07,665
Hear me out.

182
00:12:07,748 --> 00:12:10,167
I think we're onto something. Shamanism!

183
00:12:11,293 --> 00:12:13,796
But… what exactly is saju?

184
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:15,214
Isn't it your birthdate?

185
00:12:16,841 --> 00:12:18,092
Should we ask Do Hye-ryung?

186
00:12:20,511 --> 00:12:22,263
If you don't want to do it, back out.

187
00:12:23,097 --> 00:12:24,431
Stop distracting everyone.

188
00:12:28,769 --> 00:12:29,728
Hey, Si-won.

189
00:12:31,814 --> 00:12:33,607
Fuck me, that bitch is scary.

190
00:12:49,999 --> 00:12:51,292
What did I say?

191
00:12:51,792 --> 00:12:56,171
I told you, didn't I?
You were itching to come to my place.

192
00:12:57,756 --> 00:13:00,217
Shall I leave this here?

193
00:13:00,301 --> 00:13:01,385
Oh, that?

194
00:13:02,177 --> 00:13:04,138
Go leave it in that room over there.

195
00:13:08,392 --> 00:13:14,315
You've been dying to know
what's in there since last time, right?

196
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:17,234
Go ahead.

197
00:13:36,337 --> 00:13:37,588
What are you doing?

198
00:13:38,172 --> 00:13:41,592
You think I told you to go in there
just to stare at stuff?

199
00:14:07,201 --> 00:14:09,745
It's strangely soothing, isn't it?

200
00:14:47,408 --> 00:14:48,659
They're cute.

201
00:14:49,243 --> 00:14:50,869
Pick one.

202
00:14:52,246 --> 00:14:53,580
It's a gift.

203
00:15:10,472 --> 00:15:11,432
That's the one

204
00:15:11,932 --> 00:15:13,809
you were drawn to the most?

205
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:17,855
What's the name of this one?

206
00:15:17,938 --> 00:15:18,772
Deolmi.

207
00:15:19,898 --> 00:15:24,194
You grab the scruff of someone's neck,
dwitdeolmi, like this,

208
00:15:24,278 --> 00:15:26,447
and shake them however you want.

209
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:27,698
Hence the name "deolmi."

210
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:30,659
You can do it too.

211
00:15:30,743 --> 00:15:31,952
Sorry?

212
00:15:32,036 --> 00:15:35,205
I'm saying you can grab them
and shake them however you want.

213
00:15:39,334 --> 00:15:40,210
Here.

214
00:15:41,587 --> 00:15:47,259
Take something that belongs
to the person you want to grab by deolmi.

215
00:15:47,968 --> 00:15:51,263
Preferably their nails, toenails, or hair.

216
00:15:51,346 --> 00:15:53,932
Tie that thing to the doll
with the silk thread.

217
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:57,895
Then carve out the eyes, nose,
and mouth on the face,

218
00:15:58,729 --> 00:15:59,980
write down their saju here,

219
00:16:00,689 --> 00:16:04,401
and spray it all over
until the silk thread turns red…

220
00:16:04,902 --> 00:16:06,612
-Spray what?
-Blood.

221
00:16:07,196 --> 00:16:09,031
Come on, you're kidding.

222
00:16:09,114 --> 00:16:10,532
I'm not joking.

223
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:14,495
Warm, fresh blood
that still has life in it.

224
00:16:32,805 --> 00:16:34,431
I told you, didn't I?

225
00:16:34,515 --> 00:16:36,183
You're special.

226
00:16:36,683 --> 00:16:38,644
If you do exactly as I said,

227
00:16:38,727 --> 00:16:43,107
you can shake a person around
just like with this deolmi.

228
00:16:43,190 --> 00:16:44,942
Come on, I couldn't do that.

229
00:16:45,025 --> 00:16:47,111
Do you want to be my daughter?

230
00:16:48,112 --> 00:16:49,363
My spirit daughter.

231
00:16:52,783 --> 00:16:55,202
If you're home, you should let me know!

232
00:16:55,285 --> 00:16:57,663
What are you doing,
sneaking around like a thief?

233
00:16:58,455 --> 00:17:01,375
A thief is better than a woman
who drove her husband to death.

234
00:17:05,254 --> 00:17:06,213
Hey, Si-won.

235
00:17:07,089 --> 00:17:08,632
It's a misunderstanding. This is--

236
00:17:08,715 --> 00:17:10,592
Misunderstanding? Fuck, you were inside.

237
00:17:11,426 --> 00:17:14,138
Always acting friendly.
Gathering evidence to blackmail me?

238
00:17:14,221 --> 00:17:15,889
Why would I blackmail you?

239
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:18,392
Shut up and don't follow me.

240
00:17:52,176 --> 00:17:53,302
It's a misunderstanding.

241
00:17:53,802 --> 00:17:54,803
I mean it.

242
00:18:18,911 --> 00:18:20,037
Si-won, I'm sorry.

243
00:18:30,088 --> 00:18:33,008
Have you ever heard that if you write down
your saju and make a wish,

244
00:18:33,091 --> 00:18:34,676
it'll come true?

245
00:18:40,474 --> 00:18:42,559
Incense makes me wanna throw up.

246
00:18:42,643 --> 00:18:45,354
It disgusts me when those
who aren't any better than I am

247
00:18:45,437 --> 00:18:49,816
pity me as the daughter of a shaman
who drove her man to death.

248
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:53,862
And then there's my crazy mom,
always drinking and rambling nonstop…

249
00:18:55,405 --> 00:18:57,532
FEBRUARY 1, 2005
KWON SI-WON

250
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:07,167
I wish she were dead.

251
00:19:11,630 --> 00:19:13,048
That is my wish.

252
00:19:13,966 --> 00:19:15,884
Got any wishes you want to make?

253
00:19:17,469 --> 00:19:18,345
Huh?

254
00:19:24,351 --> 00:19:26,103
Do you have any wishes you wanna make?

255
00:19:27,938 --> 00:19:28,772
Yeah.

256
00:19:35,487 --> 00:19:37,114
I wish you'd accept my apology.

257
00:19:37,197 --> 00:19:38,365
Not that kind of thing.

258
00:19:41,201 --> 00:19:44,413
A wish you'd held onto
for a very long time.

259
00:19:46,832 --> 00:19:48,834
A wish you couldn't tell anyone

260
00:19:50,752 --> 00:19:52,629
and kept to yourself.

261
00:20:02,347 --> 00:20:03,515
I want Gi-tae…

262
00:20:05,517 --> 00:20:07,019
to be my boyfriend.

263
00:20:19,614 --> 00:20:21,950
Your biggest secret
is that you like Han Gi-tae?

264
00:20:26,997 --> 00:20:28,165
Then let's do it.

265
00:20:29,249 --> 00:20:30,167
Let's make a wish.

266
00:20:30,792 --> 00:20:31,835
How?

267
00:20:39,718 --> 00:20:40,761
My wish is that…

268
00:20:40,844 --> 00:20:42,179
MARCH 12, 2005
DO HYE-RYUNG

269
00:20:42,262 --> 00:20:44,222
…well, Gi-tae and I…

270
00:20:47,017 --> 00:20:47,851
Scratch that.

271
00:20:48,602 --> 00:20:51,063
Please make Gi-tae fall for me.

272
00:20:51,146 --> 00:20:53,357
No. I told you. That's not how you do it.

273
00:20:57,736 --> 00:20:59,738
Do it sincerely and wholeheartedly.

274
00:20:59,821 --> 00:21:02,824
Take it seriously,
like when I confessed my secret earlier.

275
00:21:03,408 --> 00:21:05,118
And from now on,

276
00:21:05,202 --> 00:21:09,373
